   "text": "Obstetrics & Gynecology Preeclampsia with Severe Features preeclampsia eclampsia magnesium-sulfate seizure-prophylaxis USMLE-style / MedKOS (ACOG hypertension in pregnancy) A 29 year old woman at 34 weeks gestation presents with blood pressure 168/112 mmHg on two readings, a severe headache with visual scotomata, and 3+ proteinuria. Deep tendon reflexes are brisk. Which of the following is the most appropriate immediate pharmacologic management to prevent the major acute neurologic complication? A. Intravenous magnesium sulfate for seizure prophylaxis, plus antihypertensive therapy, with planning for delivery B. Phenytoin loading as first line seizure prophylaxis C. Immediate diuresis with furosemide to lower blood pressure D. Expectant outpatient management with bed rest until term E. Low dose aspirin to treat the acute episode 중증 특징을 동반한 자간전증에서 자간증(경련) 예방의 1차 약물은 정맥 황산마그네슘이며, 함께 항고혈압제로 혈압을 조절하고 분만을 계획한다. Phenytoin은 MgSO4보다 열등하고, 이뇨제·기대요법·아스피린은 급성기 처치가 아니다."
