   "text": "Endocrinology Pheochromocytoma pheochromocytoma catecholamine alpha-blockade unopposed-alpha MEN2 USMLE-style / MedKOS (Endocrine Society pheochromocytoma guideline) A 45 year old woman has 6 months of episodic pounding headaches, palpitations, and diaphoresis. BP is 190/112 mmHg. Plasma free metanephrines are markedly elevated and abdominal CT shows a 4 cm right adrenal mass. Adrenalectomy is planned. Which of the following is the most appropriate preoperative pharmacologic preparation? A. Start propranolol first, then add phenoxybenzamine once heart rate is controlled B. Start phenoxybenzamine (alpha blockade) with volume expansion, then add a beta blocker after adequate alpha blockade C. Start metoprolol alone D. Proceed directly to surgery without medical preparation E. Start lisinopril alone 갈색세포종은 수술 전 반드시 alpha 차단(phenoxybenzamine)을 먼저 하고 용적을 보충한 뒤, 반사·잔여 빈맥에 대해 beta 차단을 나중에 추가한다. beta를 먼저 쓰면 unopposed alpha 혈관수축으로 고혈압 위기가 유발된다."
